    <stitle>13 SPEED AND 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-713/18 SERIES - REMOVE - COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="4">
        <title>COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>Both countershafts are removed the same.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>As the countershaft strap is removed, the countershaft can fall.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To keep the auxiliary countershafts from turning, place a shop rag or equivalent between the
                auxiliary drive gear and one countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300767">Figure 67</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300767" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300767" filename="../figg13/g1300767.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 67. Loosen Bolt and Retainer on Output Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the 15/16" bolt and retainer on the output shaft. Do not remove the bolt (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300767">Figure 67</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a soft bar and maul to drive the output shaft forward far enough to partially unseat the
                bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300768">Figure 68</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300768" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300768" filename="../figg13/g1300768.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 68. Drive Output Shaft Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Support the auxiliary countershaft while removing the auxiliary countershaft retaining strap
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300769">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300769" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300769" filename="../figg13/g1300769.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 69. Remove Auxiliary Countershaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary countershaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300769">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the auxiliary countershaft bearing race from the bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300769">Figure 69</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If necessary, secure the countershaft assemblies in a vise and remove both the front and
                rear bearings with a bearing separator and jaw pullers (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1300770">Figure 70</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1300770" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1300770" filename="../figg13/g1300770.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 70. Remove Front and Rear Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
